main event: A bright pinkish object, three-quarters the size of the moon, was observed zigzagging across the sky over Santa Susana, California on December 2, 1965.
interesting points: The object was observed for 2 hours, from 7:15 PM to 8:45 PM.
The object's size was estimated to be three-quarters the size of the moon.
The object appeared to have a zigzag course, but no information was provided about its altitude.
The weather was clear at the time of the sighting.
The report was filed by the Operations Staff Officer of the 6592d Support Group of the United States Air Force.
sighted object: bright pinkish object, three-quarters the size of the moon
